# Local LLM Configuration — agape-sovereign workspace
#
# PRIMARY FALLBACK MODEL: Ollama gemma4:e4b (local, no cloud, unlimited tokens)
# When Antigravity IDE's default cloud models are exhausted or unavailable,
# this workspace uses Ollama with gemma4:e4b exclusively.
#
# Rules:
# - If the default model (Claude Sonnet / Gemini) reports rate limits or token exhaustion,
#   switch to Provider: Ollama, Model: gemma4:e4b
# - DO NOT fall back to any cloud-based unlimited-token provider (OpenRouter, OpenAI, etc.)
# - Ollama endpoint: http://localhost:11434 (always local, no network egress)
# - Keep model in memory: OLLAMA_KEEP_ALIVE=-1 (persistent across sessions)
# - Context window: 8192 tokens (set via OLLAMA_NUM_CTX)
#
# Fallback order:
#   1. Default Antigravity IDE model (cloud, limited tokens)
#   2. Ollama gemma4:e4b (LOCAL ONLY — this is the hard stop; no further cloud fallback)
#
# This policy is intentional: no cloud provider should receive unlimited token requests
# without explicit user approval per session.

## Model Hierarchy
- **Primary**: Antigravity IDE default (Claude Sonnet 4.6 / Gemini)
- **Fallback**: `ollama:gemma4:e4b` via http://localhost:11434
- **No cloud overflow**: If Ollama is unavailable, stop and notify user
